d valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Blowing your shot at a Maidens Eye Shard</span><hr size=1> Here's some quick tips for anyone that wants to maximize their frustration with this part of the Vex Thal quest:<br>
<br>
1.  Join a pickup group<br>
<br>
2.  Do not mention how much you value the Shard Piece until it drops.  Better yet, don't say anything at all for the entire session.  These under-equipped, under-skilled players don't deserve your respect.<br>
<br>
3.  When you do discuss the value of the shard, force your opinion on the group.  Don't explain how and why the Vex Thal key is so difficult, just tell the group that they'll never need shard and if they give you any lip, call them fucktards.<br>
<br>
4.  Roll on all the normal loot.<br>
<br>
Do these things, and you'll greatly increase the chances that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> your</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> random pickup group will decide to lotto the shard among all the members, maximizing the chances that your ME shard will end up rotting in someone's bank account.<br>
<br>
... In the likely event that you really want the group to default the shard to you, I recommend discussing the shard with each and every pickup group you join.. long before a shard ever drops.  This way, if they have any questions, you can answer them without the pressure of a piece of loot in front them.  They may even appreciate spoiler info about the quest, and gladly reward you with the shard in return for the information.<br>
<br>
Be polite, respectful, and offer to pass on all rolls except the shard.  At the very least pass on all cash/twink rolls.<br>
<br>
The point is that losing a shard because of an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> ignorant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> group is no one's fault but your own.  If the group knows that you need the shard and knows why you need the shard, and knows how worthless the shard is to them, yet still decides not to let you have it, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> then</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> complain.  Otherwise you'll just look like a spoiled uber lootwhore. <p><center>
